  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Psychosocial Assistance  Support Services (PASS)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">War Child Canada will provide psychosocial support to the beneficiaries who have been affected by the Covid-19 pandemic. During the 6 months proposed duration of this project, War Child Canada will provide services to 6,336 individuals in Qarabagh, Dehsabz, Bagrami, and district 5th of Kabul Province. The major activities will include 1) Provision of high-quality PSS support through experienced PSS counsellors, 2) Improve and adjust the already developed PSS tools, IEC materials, and PSS delivery guidelines for PSS counsellors, 3) Establish coordination and collaborative partnership with key stakeholders, 4) Identify vulnerable population under stress and offer home-based PSS, 5) Establish monitoring and evidence-based data system, and 6) Establish SOPs for referral and establish referral linkages with service providers. All these activities are done to ensure the project is meeting the goal which is &quot;To ensure well-being and protection of vulnerable women, men, boys and adolescent girls through provision of quality psychosocial support, and multi-sectoral services in communities of Kabul Province&quot;. This will strengthen the protection mechanisms at the community level in all the target districts of Kabul to address the threats of Covid-19 outbreak.</narrative>
  </description>
